# AI Virtual Painter

**Hand Gesture-Based Drawing Application using Computer Vision**

---

## Overview

AI Virtual Painter is a real-time computer vision application that enables users to draw on a digital canvas using hand gestures captured through a webcam. The system tracks finger movements and translates them into smooth drawing strokes, eliminating the need for traditional input devices such as a mouse or stylus.

---

## Features

* Real-time hand tracking
* Gesture-based drawing (index finger)
* Mode switching using hand gestures (drawing and selection)
* Interactive color palette
* Adjustable brush size
* Adjustable eraser size
* Circular brush rendering for smooth strokes
* Canvas clearing functionality
* Save drawings as image files
* Basic shape detection (circle, rectangle, triangle)

---

## Technologies Used

* Python
* OpenCV (image processing and rendering)
* MediaPipe (hand landmark detection)
* NumPy (numerical operations)

---

## Installation

### 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/ai-virtual-painter.git
cd ai-virtual-painter
```

### 2. Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install opencv-python mediapipe numpy
```

---

## Usage

Run the application:

```bash
python painter.py
```

---

## Controls

| Input                 | Action                          |
| --------------------- | ------------------------------- |
| Index finger          | Draw                            |
| Index + Middle finger | Selection mode                  |
| Top palette area      | Change color                    |
| Black color           | Activate eraser                 |
| `[` / `]`             | Decrease / Increase brush size  |
| `-` / `+`             | Decrease / Increase eraser size |
| Clear button          | Reset canvas                    |
| `S` key               | Save drawing                    |
| `ESC`                 | Exit application                |

